# Billing & Payment Invariants (I-PAY-1 … I-PAY-12)

Scope: organization billing profiles/defaults, manual invoice drafts (agency manual billing), future Stripe-routed invoice drafts, platform fees (future), and **strict separation from model-facing surfaces**.

## I-PAY-1 — Canonical booking state as invoice basis

When invoice or payment features exist, amounts and commercial truth **must** come from canonical DB state (`getCanonicalAgreedPrice`, `option_requests`, `booking_events`, billing tables) — **not** from stale frontend cache alone.

## I-PAY-2 — Editable drafts (when invoices exist)

Auto-generated invoice drafts are **suggestions**. Line items, taxes, and totals must remain **user-editable** without mutating canonical `option_requests` negotiation fields unless explicitly designed otherwise.

## I-PAY-3 — Owner-scoped billing settings

`organization_billing_profiles` and `organization_billing_defaults` are **owner write**; RLS uses `is_org_owner(organization_id)`. Org members may **read** per policy where needed for future invoice UI.

## I-PAY-4 — Explicit add-on line items

Travel, extras, and similar costs must be **explicit line items** when invoicing exists — never hidden inside agreed fee fields on `option_requests`.

## I-PAY-5 — No customer-facing invoice before terminal booking state

Invoice issuance (when built) must not precede the agreed **job-confirmed** (or product-defined terminal) lifecycle state for that booking.

## I-PAY-6 — Currency consistency

Default currency from org defaults must align with `option_requests.currency` for that booking; no silent currency switching.

## I-PAY-7 — Tax defaults are informational

Default tax hints in org defaults are **defaults** for drafts; final tax treatment remains user/accountant responsibility unless a dedicated tax engine is added.

## I-PAY-8 — Multi-address is optional

Orgs may have multiple billing identities; exactly one **default** per org where the schema requires it (partial unique index on default).

## I-PAY-9 — No custodial booking funds (principle)

The product does not hold client↔agency booking proceeds in custody. Subscription billing (Stripe) is separate from B2B booking money flows. Future card/Connect flows must preserve **direct settlement** semantics — no “float” as a product feature unless explicitly designed and compliant.

## I-PAY-10 — MODEL BILLING FIREWALL (non-negotiable)

- **Client ↔ Agency billing visibility only** for B2B billing: invoices, billing settings, platform fees, payment status, tax identifiers, bank/payment details, and client payment data.
- **Models must not** see: billing settings UI, invoice data, platform fees, payment status, tax data, or client/agency payment details in any model-facing route, API, or realtime payload.
- **Do not** add billing tables or invoice joins to model-safe selects (`OPTION_REQUEST_SELECT_MODEL_SAFE` and related paths stay price-agnostic per existing model safety contract).
- **Future Agency → Model payouts** (if ever): **separate** feature — own UI, own RLS, own tables/flows — **no** mixing with client↔agency invoice views.

## I-PAY-11 — Billing Hub UI & attention (2026-04-19)

- **Billing Hub** surfaces (invoices, settlements, presets, operational billing) are **B2B-only**; **I-PAY-10** (model firewall) and **owner-only** billing actions (checkout, destructive owner settings) remain enforced server-side — **not** UI-only.
- **Smart Attention** (or status banners) inside the Hub **must** stay in sync when the user switches **sub-tabs** if the signal depends on the active tab (reload or keyed refetch — no stale banner after navigation).
- **Commercial truth** for amounts still comes from canonical DB state (**I-PAY-1**); Hub is presentation + drafts over that truth.

## I-PAY-12 — Manual invoices (agency manual billing) — dates & PDF display

- **DB payload:** All persisted date fields on `manual_invoices` / `manual_invoice_line_items` that map to Postgres **`date`** types must be sent as **`YYYY-MM-DD`** or **`null`**. Normalize flexible user input **only at the UI persistence boundary** (`ManualInvoiceBuilderPanel` → services); do not rely on Postgres accepting locale strings (`22.5.2026` → **22008**).
- **Validation:** Non-empty values that fail parse → **do not** call insert/update for that save attempt; show the fixed English validation message (same family as other manual-billing alerts). Empty optional fields → **`null`**, not invented defaults.
- **Separation:** Changing date parsing or PDF labels must **not** alter **tax math**, **line totals**, or **`computeManualInvoiceTotals`** — display and payload shaping only unless product explicitly adds a tax engine.
- **PDF / preview:** VAT column and VAT breakdown labels show **percentage only**; raw enum-style treatment keys (`reverse_charge`, etc.) must **not** appear as user-visible PDF text (table, totals labels, or pasted into scrubbed note fields per product rules in `.cursorrules` §29.4a).

## Regression checklist (when touching billing)

- [ ] No new model-facing surface exposes billing/fee/invoice/payment fields.
- [ ] No weakening of `OPTION_REQUEST_SELECT_MODEL_SAFE` for commercial columns.
- [ ] Owner-only billing writes remain enforced in RLS.
- [ ] Manual invoice saves: date payload remains ISO-or-null at persist boundary; PDF still hides raw treatment keys in VAT UI (**I-PAY-12**).
